  },
  {
    question: "Will insurance cover online TRT?",
    answer: "Most online TRT providers <strong>do not accept insurance</strong> for testosterone therapy. You pay out-of-pocket, but many accept HSA/FSA accounts. Some providers (Hone, PeterMD) can provide documentation for potential reimbursement claims."
  },
  {
    question: "Can online TRT doctors prescribe HCG or enclomiphene?",
    answer: "Yes. Many online TRT providers offer <strong>HCG (for fertility preservation)</strong> and <strong>enclomiphene (oral testosterone booster)</strong> as alternatives or additions to traditional testosterone injections. Titan, Maximus, and PeterMD specialize in fertility-friendly protocols."
