      <h2>What Is Online TRT?</h2>
      <p><strong>Online TRT (testosterone replacement therapy)</strong> is a telehealth service that allows men with low testosterone to consult with licensed doctors via video or messaging, get prescribed FDA-approved testosterone cypionate or enanthate, receive medication delivered to their door, self-administer weekly injections at home, and monitor progress through quarterly blood work.</p>
      <p>It's the <strong>same medical treatment as in-person clinics</strong>, just delivered via telemedicine. The testosterone is identical, the doctors are equally qualified, and the results are clinically equivalent.</p>

      <h2>How Online TRT Works (Step-by-Step)</h2>
      <h3>Step 1: Sign Up & Questionnaire (5-10 minutes)</h3>
      <p>You create an account and answer questions about age, weight, height, medical history, symptoms (fatigue, low libido, muscle loss, brain fog), current medications and health conditions, and previous testosterone therapy (if any).</p>

      <h3>Step 2: Doctor Consultation (20-30 minutes)</h3>
      <p>A licensed physician reviews your questionnaire and conducts a video call (some providers like PeterMD and Hone offer face-to-face consultations) or asynchronous messaging (others like Titan and Henry Meds use secure chat). The doctor explains TRT, discusses risks/benefits, and orders blood work.</p>

      <h3>Step 3: Blood Work (3-5 days)</h3>
      <p>Two options for testing: at-home kit (finger prick test shipped to you, mail back to lab) or local lab (visit Quest Diagnostics or LabCorp near you). Tests measure total testosterone, free testosterone, estradiol, LH, FSH, PSA, CBC, and CMP.</p>

      <h3>Step 4: Prescription Approval (1-2 days)</h3>
      <p>If your testosterone is below threshold (usually 350-400 ng/dL) AND you have symptoms, the doctor writes a prescription.</p>

      <h3>Step 5: Medication Delivery (2-3 days)</h3>
      <p>Your package includes testosterone cypionate vial (10mL, 200mg/mL), syringes and needles (1mL syringes, 25-27 gauge needles), alcohol wipes and bandages, injection instructions (video tutorial), and sharps disposal container.</p>

      <h3>Step 6: Weekly Injections (At Home)</h3>
      <p>You self-inject into your thigh or glute muscle once per week. Typical dose is 100-200mg per week, injection time is 30 seconds (after prep), and pain level is minimal (similar to flu shot).</p>

      <h3>Step 7: Quarterly Monitoring</h3>
      <p>Every 3 months, you repeat blood work to ensure testosterone levels are optimized (700-1,000 ng/dL target), estrogen is controlled (aromatase inhibitor if needed), and there are no negative health impacts (red blood cell count, PSA).</p>

